","comments":[],"created_at":1784827530082274001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"0ce57907-bcba-4f4a-b4db-cc3e8dd95bf4","relation":"discovered_from","target_id":"bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a"}],"description":"## Context / Problem\nA PASS from `rebar review-plan` is supposed to end with a signed attestation (the guide: 'on a non-blocking PASS, signs an attestation'). In practice, under concurrent store activity, the review completes PASS but exits unsigned. Observed 5 times in one session (2026-07-23, session log 1b86-3286-bbf9-4a8f) while re-planning epic bbf1 with parallel reviews running: tickets 97f2-2d98-2eff-41c1, eefd-49b1-995f-488d, aff0-b0d9-e11c-4b6a, 625b-9cd1-1ce9-4e5f, and epic bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a all printed 'plan review PASSED but the attestation could not be persisted: plan review generation changed; re-review required' (src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py:121) or logged 'attestation signing failed; verdict unsigned' (src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py:738). Only reviews with zero concurrent store movement (e.g. ad44-9f46-07aa-480c's re-run) self-signed.\n\n## Mechanism (read from the tree)\nsrc/rebar/llm/plan_review/generation.py:146-154: at sign time the plan-relation generation snapshot `collect(ticket_id)` is compared against `initial_generation` captured at review START; if ANY tracked material moved during the (minutes-long) LLM review, it raises PlanReviewGenerationChanged('plan review generation changed; re-review required') and the verdict stays unsigned. But the sanctioned recovery, `rebar sign-review <id>`, then signs from the SAME REVIEW_RESULT sidecar against the CURRENT head with no LLM re-run — and the claim gate accepts it ('re-signed the plan-review attestation from the latest REVIEW_RESULT sidecar'). So the in-command fail-closed check is strictly harsher than the invariant the store actually enforces, and the message's 're-review required' is contradicted by the recovery path that needs no re-review. Under multi-agent load (many parallel review-plan/edit/comment auto-commits) the majority of passing reviews hit this and each needs a manual rescue.\n\n## Expected\nEither (a) review-plan self-heals: on PlanReviewGenerationChanged, if the ticket's own material fingerprint is unchanged (only unrelated store movement), retry the sign against the current head — i.e. run the sign-review path in-process before giving up; or (b) if a genuine material change to the ticket occurred, keep failing closed but say so specifically; and in the residual failure message, instruct 'rebar sign-review <id>' (the documented recovery) instead of 're-review required' (wrong — a re-review is not required and wastes a full LLM run).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A review-plan PASS during which only UNRELATED store writes land (another ticket's edits/comments/attestations) ends certified with no manual step — verified by a unit/integration test that commits an unrelated ticket event between review start and sign.\n- [ ] A review-plan PASS during which the reviewed ticket's own material changes still fails closed, with a message naming the ticket-material change — verified by a companion test.\n- [ ] The residual unsigned-PASS message points to 'rebar sign-review <id>', not 're-review required' — verified by asserting the CLI output text (src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py:121).\n- [ ] make lint && make typecheck && make test green.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/llm/plan_review/generation.py","reason":"generation-changed fail-closed at sign time (lines 146-154): distinguish unrelated store movement from ticket-material change; retry sign"},{"path":"src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py","reason":"unsigned-PASS message (line 121): point to rebar sign-review, drop the wrong re-review-required claim"},{"path":"src/rebar/llm/plan_review/resign.py","reason":"reuse the sidecar re-sign path in-process on recoverable generation changes"},{"path":"tests/","reason":"unrelated-write vs own-material-change signing tests + CLI message assertion"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"81c9c8f3-366e-4b9a-b3c2-430e34fa8fd2","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"790c-a7a3-120a-42c8","ticket_type":"bug","title":"review-plan: passing review frequently ends unsigned under concurrent store writes; error demands re-review although sign-review certifies from the same sidecar","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["4a6767a5-2c88-4767-9d06-5b3ac81af3ab","34574740-489c-4771-8803-35901bf63505","0ce57907-bcba-4f4a-b4db-cc3e8dd95bf4","81c9c8f3-366e-4b9a-b3c2-430e34fa8fd2","70124ca8-5fad-4e77-97f3-fcdd465bd537","8516f615-7e6b-44c9-b6b6-dfe90c8eba50"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784828748285877478,"uuid":"d196508b-1e8d-4392-8922-8d51f46ea589"}